    "faqs": [
      {
        "question": "Does an MRI screening of joints hurt?",
        "answer": "No. You simply lie still; there is no needle unless contrast is required.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "How soon can I drive after the scan?",
        "answer": "Immediately—no sedatives are used for routine joint MRIs.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "Can I eat before the scan?",
        "answer": "Yes. Fasting is only needed for abdominal scans, not joints.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "What if I’m claustrophobic?",
        "answer": "Our wide-bore MRI scanners and in-room music reduce anxiety; mild sedation can be arranged on request."
      },
      {
        "question": "Will insurance cover the cost?",
        "answer": "Most policies cover medically indicated joint MRIs; our front desk assists with pre-authorisation.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "What is the approximate cost of a multi-joint MRI screening?",
        "answer": "The **Multi-joint MRI screening cost and procedure** involves both the scan itself and the radiologist's interpretation. The cost can vary depending on the number of joint areas included in the screening protocol and the specifics of the examination at **Cadabams Diagnostics**.\n\n"
      }
    ],
